This paper deals with the analysis of deep ReLU networks and their generalization properties. The most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper focuses on the learning dynamics and generalization of deep neural networks. The second likely sub-category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as the paper analyzes the behavior of neural networks. The third likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as deep neural networks are widely used in computer vision tasks. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with the analysis of deep neural networks. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper discusses the training dynamics of deep neural networks.
